  <h4><a href="http://www.democracynow.org/blog/2010/12/11/video_un_guards_beat_reuters_photographer_at_cancn_climate_talks">Video: U.N. Guards Beat Reuters Photographer at Cancún Climate Talks</a></h4>
  <p><img alt="Reutersjournalistdetainedandbeaten" src="/resources/thumbnails/25/425/ReutersJournalistDetainedAndBeaten.jpg" /> <em>Democracy Now!</em> videotaped U.N. security guards Friday beating a Reuters photographer who was arrested while covering a protest at the U.N. climate conference in Cancún. Guards seized Jorge Silva&#8217;s press credentials and then beat him while he was detained on a bus. The incident sparked a protest by other Mexican photographers. <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2i0LmDE73jc">Watch video</a></p>
  <p class="posted">Filed under <a href="http://www.democracynow.org/blog/category/web_exclusive">Web Exclusive</a></p>
